  <ol id="questionList">
    <li id="q1">How many people spoke three languages in 2001?
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a1">1 million</a></li>
		<li><a id="a2">1.5 million</a></li>
		<li><a id="a3">3 million</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q2">The number of people who spoke two languages (...) between 1960 and 2001.				
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a4">decreased by 500,000</a></li>
		<li><a id="a5">remained the same</a></li>
		<li><a id="a6">increased by 500,000</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q3">What does this graph show?
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a7">the number of people in the population who had language disorders</a></li>
		<li><a id="a8">the number of people in the population who did not have language disorders</a></li>
		<li><a id="a9">the proportion of the population who had language disorders</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q4">In 1981 (...) had language disorders.
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a10">500,000 people</a></li>
		<li><a id="a11">5 in every 100,000 people</a></li>
		<li><a id="a12">5 per cent of the population</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q5">Approximately how many students studied Italian in 1987?
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a13">30</a></li>
		<li><a id="a14">80</a></li>
		<li><a id="a15">180</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q6">Between 1997 and 2002 the number of students of Italian (...).
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a16">fell</a></li>
		<li><a id="a17">remained the same</a></li>
		<li><a id="a18">rose</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q7">How much time did the majority of 19 to 25-year-olds spend on the telephone each week?
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a19">less than 1 hour</a></li>
		<li><a id="a20">1 to 3 hours</a></li>
		<li><a id="a21">more than 5 hours</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q8">Which age group spent the least time on the telephone per week?
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a22">12-18</a></li>
		<li><a id="a23">26-45</a></li>
		<li><a id="a24">65+</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q9">How many languages were spoken in 1500?
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a25">approximately 7,000</a></li>
		<li><a id="a26">7,000</a></li>
		<li><a id="a27">approximately 9,000</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q10">What is the predicted world population in 2100?
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a28">8,000 million</a></li>
		<li><a id="a29">10,000 million</a></li>
		<li><a id="a30">80,000 million</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q11">What does this chart show?
		<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a31">the percentage of the population with e-mail and personal websites</a></li>
		<li><a id="a32">the percentage of workers who know how to use e-mail and websites</a></li>
		<li><a id="a33">the percentage of workers whose employers provide them with e-mail facilities or personal websites</a></li></list></li>
    <br/>
